<section xml:id="section-assignment3">
  <title>Assignment 3</title>
  <p><ol>
    <li>
      <p>
        Write these cartesian loci as polar loci. (6) 
        <ol>
          <li><me>
            4x + 5y = 1 
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            \frac{1}{3x^2 + 3y^2 + 4} = 7 
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            \frac{y}{x} + x^2 + y^2 = 7
          </me></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Write these cartesian loci as spherical loci. (6) 
        <ol>
          <li><me>
            4x + 3y - 5z = 4
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            \frac{1}{x^2 + y^2 + z^2} - \sqrt{x^2 + y^2 + z^2} = 3 
          </me></li>
          <li><me>
            \frac{5z}{\sqrt{x^2 + y^2}} - x^2 - y^2 - z^2 = 4 
          </me></li>
        </ol>
      </p>
    </li>
    <li>
      <p>
        Consider this parametric curve (in cartesian coordinates). (6) 
        <me>
          \gamma(t) = (e^{t+1}, e^{t-1}) 
